### Test BB Agent Manager Running in Docker

# Health Check
GET http://localhost:8001/health

### List Available Tools
GET http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/tools

### Write Documentation
POST http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/invoke
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "devdocs_write",
  "arguments": {
    "filename": "copilot_test.md",
    "content": "# Copilot Integration Test\n\n## Overview\n\nTesting BB Agent Manager from GitHub Copilot!\n\n## Features\n- Write documentation\n- Read documentation\n- List all docs\n\n## Status\n✅ Working perfectly in Docker!"
  }
}

### Read Documentation
POST http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/invoke
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "devdocs_read",
  "arguments": {
    "filename": "copilot_test.md"
  }
}

### List All Documentation Files
POST http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/invoke
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "devdocs_list",
  "arguments": {}
}

### Example: Write API Documentation
POST http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/invoke
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "devdocs_write",
  "arguments": {
    "filename": "api_overview.md",
    "content": "# API Overview\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API requests require authentication using Bearer tokens.\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN\" \\\n  http://localhost:8001/agent/mcp/tools\n```\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### GET /health\nReturns service health status\n\n### GET /agent/mcp/tools\nList all available tools\n\n### POST /agent/mcp/invoke\nInvoke a specific tool with arguments"
  }
}
